Singer and actress Kelly Khumalo dropped her son Christian off for his first day back at primary school and, in an emotional Instagram post, wished her son well in his dream to become a pilot."As he gets ready for school, a big part of me is extremely happy yet emotional. We have come a long way my boy. Yes, you and I fight every five minutes because of your extra ordinary character but then again I didn't ask God for a normal boy. "Last week, I asked what you wanted to be when you grow up, you said you want fly aeroplane, Well, son, your journey of becoming a pilot begins today," she wrote. Other celebrities, including, L'vovo, Muvhango actress Maduvha Madima and Chad Saaiman also posted pictures or videos on social media of themselves dropping off their little ones at school. A photo posted by Chad Saaiman (@chadsaaiman) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:44pm PST A photo posted by Chad Saaiman (@chadsaaiman) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:44pm PST A video posted by Maduvha Madima (@maduvha_madima) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:31pm PST A video posted by Maduvha Madima (@maduvha_madima) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:31pm PST A photo posted by Lvovo Derrango (@lvovosa) on Jan 10, 2017 at 9:06pm PST A photo posted by Lvovo Derrango (@lvovosa) on Jan 10, 2017 at 9:06pm PSTComedian Mpho Pops, DJ Sbu and actress Millicent Makhado were among the celebs who dropped their kids off for the first day of pre-school. A photo posted by #SLEFBenefitConcert4thFeb (@djsbulive) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:04pm PSTA photo posted by #SLEFBenefitConcert4thFeb (@djsbulive) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:04pm PST A photo posted by Mpho Modikoane (@mphopopps) on Jan 10, 2017 at 9:56pm PST A photo posted by Mpho Modikoane (@mphopopps) on Jan 10, 2017 at 9:56pm PST A photo posted by Millicent Makhado (@millicent_makhado) on Jan 10, 2017 at 11:38pm PST A photo posted by Millicent Makhado (@millicent_makhado) on Jan 10, 2017 at 11:38pm PST A photo posted by Minki vd Westhuizen (@minkivanderwesthuizen) on Jan 10, 2017 at 10:38pm PST A photo po